You will also need to download the **Open World Demo Collection** content pack from the **Unreal Engine Marketplace** as some of the content from the collection will be used in the following Quick Start.
Once the Open World Demo Collection is downloaded add it to the project that you are using to follow along with this Quick Start by doing the following.

1. From the Epic Games Launcher in the Marketplace locate and then download the **Open World Demo Collection**.
	
	![](Engine\OpenWorldTools\T_OWT_OWDC.png)

1. Go the **Library** section of the launcher and then under **Vault** section locate the Open World Demo Collection . 
	
	![](Engine\OpenWorldTools\T_OWT_Add_Content_00.png)

1. Click on the button that says **Add to Project**.
	
	![](Engine\OpenWorldTools\T_OWT_Add_To_Project.png)

1. You will then be shown a list of projects that you can add this to, select the project that you are using to follow along with this Quick Start and then press the **Add to Project** button

	![](Engine\OpenWorldTools\T_OWT_ATP.png)

